The paper discusses foundational issues in theoretical computer science and presents them using the language of category theory. This suggests that it could belong to the category theory (cs.CT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses concepts such as computability, algorithms, and information, which are also relevant to the logic (cs.LO), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions functoriality and composition, which are important concepts in the area of computational complexity (cs.CC).
